<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Launch2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Launch,</orth> vb. (M. Edd. <emph>lance</emph>) to pierce, to cut: <cit><quote>--eth not the sore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.303" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 303</bibl></cit> (Ff Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>lanceth</emph>). <cit><quote>--ed their tender hearts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.224" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 224</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>lanched,</emph> M. Edd. <emph>lanced</emph>). <cit><quote>--ed mine arm,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 54</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>latch'd</emph>). <cit><quote>we do l. diseases in our bodies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 1, 36</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>